Redesign the ESG Profile modal for an HSBC sustainability intelligence platform called “Transition Copilot”.

The ESG Profile should represent ONLY the CURRENT sustainability state and Scope 3 intelligence of a supplier.

IMPORTANT:
This screen is NOT about:

- financing
- transition execution
- recommendations
- loans
- implementation planning

Those belong in the separate “Transition Copilot” screen.

This ESG Profile should feel like:
“AI-generated sustainability intelligence report.”

The UI should communicate:

- current emissions
- ESG condition
- sustainability maturity
- operational environmental impact
- risk visibility
- supplier sustainability intelligence

Design inspiration:

- Palantir Foundry
- Bloomberg Terminal (modernized)
- Stripe Dashboard
- Linear
- Apple-level minimalism
- Perplexity AI

The UI should feel:

- premium
- intelligent
- enterprise-grade
- cinematic
- analytical
- trustworthy
- AI-native

Avoid:

- cluttered dashboards
- excessive borders
- too many cards
- financing widgets
- implementation roadmaps
- overly colorful visuals

Use:

- spacious layout
- soft depth
- layered surfaces
- elegant typography
- subtle glow
- intelligent motion
- minimal glassmorphism

